🛠️ Setup and Installation
This is a single React component file (expense_tracker_app.tsx). To run it, you typically need a standard React development environment (like Create React App or Vite).

1. Configure Your Project
Create a Project: Start a new React project (e.g., npx create-react-app finance-flow or npm create vite@latest).
Install Dependencies: This app uses lucide-react for icons and recharts for charts.

npm install lucide-react recharts tailwindcss
# If using Vite/CRA, ensure you configure Tailwind CSS

Place the Code: Replace the content of your main application file (e.g., src/App.jsx or src/App.tsx) with the content of expense_tracker_app.tsx.

2. Set Up the Gemini API Key
The application needs a Gemini API key to run the AI features.
Get your key from Google AI Studio.
In a standard React environment, you should use a .env file for secrets.
Create a file named .env in your project root.
Add your API key:
REACT_APP_GEMINI_API_KEY="YOUR_API_KEY_HERE"
Update the Component: In expense_tracker_app.tsx, replace the hardcoded apiKey variable with the environment variable reference:

// expense_tracker_app.tsx (Update this line)// const apiKey = ""; 
const apiKey = process.env.REACT_APP_GEMINI_API_KEY || "";
If you are running this in a protected environment (like the one where this file was generated), the original empty string const apiKey = "" will be automatically handled.

3. Run the Application
npm start   # or npm run dev for Vite
Open your browser to the specified port (usually http://localhost:3000).

